title: MQM’s Saeed Anwar wins PS-101 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Mutahidda Quomi Movement (MQM) candidate Saeed Anwar has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-101, Karachi, East V, by securing 43,080 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Agha Arsalan Khan, who bagged, 34,745 votes.
Voters’ turn-out remained 41.75 percent.
